cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with camera localization, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of synthesized images and their comparison to real images could also place the paper in cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper's focus on tracking systems and localization could suggest that it belongs to cs.RO (Robotics).
